parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes feel spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the brakes fail to engage when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes feel spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the brakes fail to engage when needed
especially when driving over bumps or rough roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes feel spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the brakes fail to engage when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to hesitate, lose power, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power when accelerating
especially when merging onto a highway or turning left across traffic. The transmission may slip or jerk
causing the vehicle to lunge forward or stall. The vehicle may also experience a sudden loss of acceleration or power
making it difficult to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
especially when accelerating from a stop
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the vehicle stalls or refuses to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, shattering of glass, and potentially distract the driver, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The sunroof suddenly shatters or explodes
often with a loud noise
without any apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to accelerate properly can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or accelerating from a stop.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to accelerate
especially when merging into traffic or accelerating from a stop
the vehicle lurches forward suddenly
the vehicle has difficulty maintaining speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the visor to stay in place can cause a distraction or obstruction of the driver's view, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The visor falls or does not stay in place
obstructing the driver's view
especially when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
especially when accelerating from a stop
the electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle's lights or accessories fail to function.
